        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-[#333333] mt-12 mb-6">What Is Deep Cleaning vs. Regular Cleaning?</h2>

        <p>
          Before we talk numbers, let's clarify what deep cleaning actually means. Regular cleaning—your typical weekly or biweekly service—maintains a home that's already clean. Surfaces get wiped, floors get mopped, bathrooms get scrubbed. It keeps things presentable.
        </p>

        <p>
          Deep cleaning goes much further. It targets the grime that builds up over months or years in places you rarely think about: inside the oven, behind the toilet, on top of ceiling fan blades, inside window tracks, under the refrigerator. It's the reset button for your home.
        </p>

        <p>
          In the Shoals area, where humidity can encourage mold growth and Alabama red clay seems to get everywhere, deep cleaning addresses problems specific to our region. Homes in Florence near the Tennessee River or Muscle Shoals near Wilson Dam often deal with moisture-related buildup that requires extra attention.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-[#333333] mt-12 mb-6">Deep Cleaning Costs in the Shoals: What to Expect</h2>

        <p>
          Based on current market rates in the Quad Cities area, here's what homeowners typically pay for professional deep cleaning:
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#333333] mt-8 mb-4">By Home Size</h3>

