          <li><strong>3 Bedroom (1,200–1,800 sq ft):</strong> $275–$375</li>
          <li><strong>4 Bedroom (1,800–2,500 sq ft):</strong> $350–$450</li>
          <li><strong>5+ Bedroom (2,500+ sq ft):</strong> $450–$600+</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          These ranges apply across Florence, Muscle Shoals, Tuscumbia, and Sheffield. Prices in nearby areas like Killen, Rogersville, and Leighton typically fall within the same range, though some companies charge travel fees for locations outside the immediate Quad Cities.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#333333] mt-8 mb-4">By Hourly Rate</h3>

        <p>
          Some cleaning services charge by the hour rather than by the project. In the Shoals area, expect:
        </p>

        <ul class="space-y-3 mb-8">
          <li><strong>Solo cleaner:</strong> $35–$50 per hour</li>
          <li><strong>Two-person team:</strong> $60–$90 per hour</li>
          <li><strong>Professional crew (3+):</strong> $90–$125 per hour</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          A deep clean typically takes 4–8 hours depending on home size and condition. At The Valley Clean Team, we prefer flat-rate pricing so there are no surprises—the price we quote is the price you pay.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-[#333333] mt-12 mb-6">Factors That Affect Deep Cleaning Cost</h2>

        <p>
          Why such a wide range in pricing? Several factors determine where your home falls on the spectrum:
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#333333] mt-8 mb-4">1. Time Since Last Deep Clean</h3>

        <p>
          A home that gets deep cleaned quarterly is much faster to service than one that hasn't been professionally cleaned in years. Built-up grease in the kitchen, soap scum in showers, and dust accumulation all add time—and therefore cost.
        </p>

        <p>
          If your Florence or Muscle Shoals home hasn't had professional cleaning in over a year, expect pricing toward the higher end of the range.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#333333] mt-8 mb-4">2. Number of Bathrooms</h3>

        <p>
          Bathrooms take the most time during deep cleaning. Tile grout, shower doors, behind toilets, exhaust fans, under vanities—there's a lot of detail work. Homes with 3+ bathrooms typically cost $50–$100 more than comparable homes with fewer.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#333333] mt-8 mb-4">3. Kitchen Condition</h3>

        <p>
          The kitchen is usually the second most labor-intensive area. Inside the oven, refrigerator coils, range hood filters, cabinet fronts, and behind appliances all require attention. Kitchens with heavy grease buildup can add an hour or more to the job.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#333333] mt-8 mb-4">4. Pets</h3>

        <p>
          We love animals—many Shoals families have dogs and cats—but pets add work. Pet hair accumulates in corners, on furniture, and in vents. Pet-related odors may require extra treatment. Most services add $25–$75 for homes with pets.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#333333] mt-8 mb-4">5. Clutter Level</h3>

        <p>
          Professional cleaners need to access surfaces to clean them. Homes with significant clutter require more time to work around items. Some services charge extra; others ask clients to declutter before the appointment.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#333333] mt-8 mb-4">6. Add-On Services</h3>

        <p>
          Standard deep cleaning covers the essentials. Additional services that often cost extra include:
        </p>

        <ul class="space-y-2 mb-8">
          <li>Interior window cleaning: $50–$150</li>
          <li>Inside refrigerator/freezer: $25–$50</li>
          <li>Inside oven cleaning: $25–$50</li>
          <li>Laundry and folding: $25–$50 per load</li>
          <li>Organizing services: $40–$75 per hour</li>
          <li>Garage cleaning: $75–$200</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-[#333333] mt-12 mb-6">What's Included in a Deep Cleaning?</h2>

