        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-[#333333] mt-12 mb-6">Shoals-Specific Considerations</h2>

        <p>
          Living in the Quad Cities comes with unique cleaning challenges:
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#333333] mt-8 mb-4">Humidity and Moisture</h3>

        <p>
          The Tennessee River runs right through our area. Florence sits along the banks, and Muscle Shoals, Tuscumbia, and Sheffield are all river-adjacent. This proximity means higher humidity, which can lead to mold and mildew in bathrooms, closets, and basements.
        </p>

        <p>
          A quality deep clean addresses moisture-related buildup. Bathroom exhaust fans get cleaned and tested, shower caulk gets inspected, and problem areas get flagged before they become major issues.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#333333] mt-8 mb-4">Alabama Red Clay</h3>

        <p>
          That distinctive red soil gets tracked into homes throughout the Shoals. It stains grout, embeds in carpet, and clings to baseboards. Professional deep cleaning can address clay buildup that regular cleaning doesn't fully remove.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#333333] mt-8 mb-4">Older Homes</h3>

        <p>
          The Shoals has beautiful historic homes, especially in downtown Florence and the older sections of Tuscumbia and Sheffield. Older homes often have details—crown molding, built-in shelving, original hardwood—that require careful attention. Quality cleaning services adjust their approach for these architectural features.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-[#333333] mt-12 mb-6">How to Get the Best Value</h2>

        <p>
          Price matters, but value matters more. Here's how to ensure you're getting quality for your money:
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#333333] mt-8 mb-4">Check Insurance and Bonding</h3>

        <p>
          Any professional cleaning service should carry liability insurance. At The Valley Clean Team, we carry $2 million in liability coverage—not the bare minimum $500,000 that many services carry. This protects your home and your belongings.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#333333] mt-8 mb-4">Ask About Consistency</h3>

        <p>
          Will you get the same cleaning team each visit? Consistency matters for quality. Our "same team, every time" policy means your cleaners know your home, your preferences, and your standards.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#333333] mt-8 mb-4">Look for Transparent Pricing</h3>

        <p>
          Be wary of quotes that seem vague or companies that won't provide written estimates. The price you're quoted should be the price you pay—no hidden fees, no surprise charges.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#333333] mt-8 mb-4">Read Local Reviews</h3>

        <p>
          Check Google reviews, Facebook, and local community groups. Shoals residents are quick to share both positive and negative experiences with local service providers.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#333333] mt-8 mb-4">Consider Bundling</h3>

        <p>
          Many cleaning services offer discounts when you bundle deep cleaning with ongoing service. Starting with a deep clean and transitioning to regular maintenance is often the most cost-effective approach long-term.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-[#333333] mt-12 mb-6">When Should You Get a Deep Clean?</h2>

        <p>
          Most Shoals homeowners benefit from professional deep cleaning in these situations:
        </p>

        <ul class="space-y-3 mb-8">
          <li><strong>Seasonally:</strong> Spring and fall are popular times for deep cleaning—once before summer entertaining season and once before holiday gatherings</li>
          <li><strong>After construction or renovation:</strong> Even with contractor cleanup, fine dust settles everywhere</li>
          <li><strong>Before moving in:</strong> Start fresh in your new Florence, Muscle Shoals, or Tuscumbia home</li>
          <li><strong>After illness:</strong> Reset the home after flu season or other illness</li>
          <li><strong>Before hosting guests:</strong> Make sure every corner is guest-ready</li>
          <li><strong>When switching to regular cleaning service:</strong> Deep clean first, then maintain</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-[#333333] mt-12 mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-[#333333] mt-6 mb-3">How long does a deep cleaning take?</h3>
        <p>
          For a typical 3-bedroom home in the Shoals, expect 4–6 hours with a two-person team. Larger homes or those with heavy buildup may take longer.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-[#333333] mt-6 mb-3">Do I need to be home during the cleaning?</h3>
        <p>
          No. Many of our Shoals clients provide a code, key, or smart lock access. Our teams are background-checked, insured, and bonded.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-[#333333] mt-6 mb-3">How often should I get a deep cleaning?</h3>
        <p>
          Most homes benefit from deep cleaning 2–4 times per year. If you have pets, allergies, or high household traffic, quarterly deep cleaning is ideal.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-[#333333] mt-6 mb-3">What's the difference between deep cleaning and move-out cleaning?</h3>
        <p>
          Move-out cleaning is a specific type of deep cleaning focused on preparing a property for the next tenant or buyer. It often includes inside all cabinets and closets, even if empty.
        </p>

